post_text:
Meet the staff! Math teacher, Mrs. Riesterer

‚ÄúMath is a tough subject, and finishing up multiple credits to prepare for graduation is no joke! Still, Mr. Clark and I are committed to helping every student power through and the fun moments along the way keep us going when the work gets hard. To help students, I love preparing little charts, notes and videos for reference. Even better is when we get to work through things together, discussing tips and tricks for solving different types of problems. Despite whatever this pandemic may throw at us during this next year, we're excited to find creative ways to continue earning credits while building the relationships with students that make all of our hard work worth it. We've missed you all but I look forward to getting back in the classroom for another fun year together!‚Äù

Meet The Staff: Next up is Assistant Director Ms. Eisel!

‚ÄúThis will be my 14th year in education. Prior to becoming Assistant Director at Franklinton Prep, I worked the previous two years under Mr. Mintos at Central High. Before that I was an English teacher for 11 years. In May, I graduated with my masters in educational leadership from Ohio Dominican University.

Last school year I loved watching all of the phlebotomy students learn real-life job skills! It was fun to see them start out so nervous, but then walk away as confident adults ready to join the workforce! I can‚Äôt wait for this year‚Äôs round of new phlebotomy students!‚Äù

post_text:
Meet the Staff: first up, Mr. Mintos- Director

‚ÄúI get the most enjoyment seeing the faces of graduates as they line up right before the ceremony begins. It is a pensive look as the student prepares for their life to shift. In their faces I can see every spirited conversation we had, every time they wanted to give up, every time their heart was broken. To see them standing proud about their journey through every negative obstacle to get to that celebratory moment, it reminds me that everyone‚Äôs story is worth telling. I love seeing that range of emotions shine through.‚Äù
